\v 21  \wj \+w but\+w* \+w the\+w* person \+w who\+w* lives \+w by\+w* \+w the\+w* truth \+w comes\+w* \+w into\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w light\+w*, \+w so\+w* \+w it\+w* \+w can\+w* \+w be\+w* clearly seen \+w that\+w* \+w God\+w* \+w is\+w* \+w in\+w* \+w all\+w* \+w they\+w* \+w do\+w*.\wj* 
\b
\p
\v 22 After this, Jesus went with his disciples into the country parts of Judea; and there he stayed with them, and baptized. 
\v 23 John, also, was baptizing at Aenon near Salim, because there were many streams there; and people were constantly coming and being baptized. 
\v 24 (For John had not yet been imprisoned). 
\v 25 Now a discussion arose between some of John’s disciples and a fellow Jew on the subject of purification; 
\v 26 and the disciples came to John and said, ‘Rabbi, the man who was with you on the other side of the Jordan, and to whom you have yourself borne testimony – he, also, is baptizing, and everybody is going to him.’ 
\v 27 John’s answer was – ‘A person can gain nothing but what is given them from heaven. 
\v 28 You are yourselves witnesses that I said “I am not the Christ,” but “I have been sent before him as a messenger.” 
\v 29 It is the groom who has the bride; but the groom’s friend, who stands by and listens to him, is filled with joy when he hears the groom’s voice. This joy I have felt to the full. 
\v 30 He must become greater, and I less.’ 
\p
\v 31 He who comes from above is above all others; but a child of earth is earthly, and his teaching is earthly, too. He who comes from heaven is above all others. 
\v 32 He states what he has seen and what he heard, and yet no one accepts his statement. 
\v 33 They who did accept his statement confirm the fact that God is true. 
\v 34 For he whom God sent as his messenger gives us God’s own teaching, for God does not limit the gift of the Spirit. 
\v 35 The Father loves his Son, and has put everything in his hands. 
\v 36 The person who believes in the Son has eternal life, while a person who rejects the Son will not even see that life, but remains under God’s displeasure. 
\c 4  
\b
\p
\v 1 Now, when the Master heard that the Pharisees had been told that he was making and baptizing more disciples than John 
\v 2 (Though it was not Jesus himself, but his disciples, who baptized), 
\v 3 he left Judea, and set out again for Galilee. 
\v 4 He had to pass through Samaria, 
\v 5 and, on his way, he came to a Samaritan town called Shechem, near the plot of land that Jacob gave to his son Joseph. 
\v 6 Jacob’s Spring was there, and Jesus, being tired after his journey, sat down beside the spring, just as he was. It was then about midday. 
\v 7 A woman of Samaria came to draw water; and Jesus said to her – \wj ‘\+w Give\+w* \+w me\+w* \+w some\+w* \+w to\+w* \+w drink\+w*,’\wj* 
\v 8 For his disciples had gone into the town to buy food. 
\v 9 ‘How is it,’ replied the Samaritan woman, ‘that you who are a Jew ask for water from a Samaritan woman like me?’ (For Jews do not associate with Samaritans). 
\v 10  \wj ‘\+w If\+w* \+w you\+w* \+w knew\+w* \+w of\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w gift\+w* \+w of\+w* \+w God\+w*,’\wj* replied Jesus, \wj ‘\+w and\+w* \+w who\+w* \+w it\+w* \+w is\+w* \+w that\+w* \+w is\+w* \+w saying\+w* \+w to\+w* \+w you\+w* “\+w Give\+w* \+w me\+w* \+w some\+w* \+w water\+w*,” \+w you\+w* \+w would\+w* \+w have\+w* \+w asked\+w* \+w him\+w*, \+w and\+w* \+w he\+w* \+w would\+w* \+w have\+w* \+w given\+w* \+w you\+w* \+w living\+w* \+w water\+w*.’\wj* 
\p
\v 11 ‘You have no bucket, Sir, and the well is deep,’ she said. ‘Where did you get that “living water?” 
\v 12 Surely you are not greater than our ancestor Jacob who gave us the well, and used to drink from it himself, and his sons, and his cattle!’ 
\p
\v 13  \wj ‘\+w All\+w* \+w who\+w* \+w drink\+w* \+w of\+w* \+w this\+w* \+w water\+w*,’\wj* replied Jesus, \wj ‘\+w will\+w* \+w be\+w* \+w thirsty\+w* \+w again\+w*;\wj* 
\v 14  \wj \+w but\+w* \+w whoever\+w* \+w once\+w* \+w drinks\+w* \+w of\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w water\+w* \+w that\+w* \+w I\+w* \+w will\+w* \+w give\+w* \+w him\+w* \+w will\+w* \+w never\+w* \+w thirst\+w* \+w any\+w* \+w more\+w*; \+w but\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w water\+w* \+w that\+w* \+w I\+w* \+w will\+w* \+w give\+w* \+w him\+w* \+w will\+w* \+w become\+w* \+w a\+w* \+w spring\+w* welling \+w up\+w* \+w within\+w* \+w him\+w* – \+w a\+w* source \+w of\+w* eternal \+w life\+w*.’\wj* 
\p
\v 15 ‘Give me this water, Sir,’ said the woman, ‘so that I may not be thirsty, nor have to come all the way here to draw water.’ 
\p
\v 16  \wj ‘\+w Go\+w* \+w and\+w* \+w call\+w* \+w your\+w* husband,’\wj* said Jesus, \wj ‘\+w and\+w* \+w then\+w* \+w come\+w* \+w back\+w*.’\wj* 
\p
\v 17 ‘I have no husband,’ answered the woman. \wj ‘\+w You\+w* \+w are\+w* \+w right\+w* \+w in\+w* \+w saying\+w* “\+w I\+w* \+w have\+w* \+w no\+w* husband,”’\wj* replied Jesus, 
\v 18  \wj ‘\+w For\+w* \+w you\+w* \+w have\+w* \+w had\+w* \+w five\+w* husbands, \+w and\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w man\+w* \+w with\+w* \+w whom\+w* \+w you\+w* \+w are\+w* \+w now\+w* \+w living\+w* \+w is\+w* \+w not\+w* \+w your\+w* husband; \+w in\+w* \+w saying\+w* \+w that\+w*, \+w you\+w* \+w have\+w* \+w spoken\+w* \+w the\+w* truth.’\wj* 
\p
\v 19 ‘I see, Sir, that you are a prophet!’ exclaimed the woman. 
\v 20 ‘It was on this mountain that our ancestors worshiped; and yet you Jews say that the proper place for worship is in Jerusalem.’ 
