\c 9  
\b
\p
\v 1 As Jesus passed by, he saw a man who had been blind from his birth. 
\v 2 ‘Rabbi,’ asked his disciples, ‘who was it that sinned, this man or his parents, that he was born blind?’ 
\p
\v 3  \wj ‘\+w Neither\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w man\+w* \+w nor\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w parents\+w*,’\wj* replied Jesus, \wj ‘\+w but\+w* \+w he\+w* \+w was\+w* born blind \+w so\+w* \+w that\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w work\+w* \+w of\+w* \+w God\+w* \+w should\+w* \+w be\+w* \+w made\+w* plain \+w in\+w* \+w him\+w*.\wj* 
